title: Road intersection traffic volume distribution
caption: Comparison between 1 January 2020 to 31 March 2020 period (baseline) and subsequent days' traffic volume across select intersections within 1 February, 2020 to 11 February, 2022 in the Austin TX.
insights: After the mid-March the overall traffic volume was reduced significantly. It then gradually increased until summer 2020 and maintains rather consistent traffic volume at about 20% below the baseline.
The holiday events (Thanks Giving, Christmas) generated local fluctuations.
Two intersections show unique changes, one of which is attributed to the volume of University of Texas at Austin student traffic at Martin Luther King Blvd / Red River St

The intersection at Airport Blvd / IH 35 SVRD intersection is unique as it shows various changes in traffic levels, attributable to it being a major intersection for a wide range of services used by central Austin residents.

source.name: Austin Transportation Department, City of Austin
